 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Associate Director, Digital Quality Resilience 6 reviews Allston, MA Resilience 6 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Ready to join a team dedicated to quality excellence, innovation and the advance of complex medicine manufacturing supporting patients worldwide? Are you an architect at heart and love designing and developing systems and processes from the ground up? We started an incredible journey and are looking for passionate leaders to join us on this important mission.
 This role is accountable for assisting in the development, implementation and lifecycle management of the Digital Quality and Compliance program and operationalizing it. The Associate Director, Digital Quality is a key leadership role and reports to the Head of Digital Quality.
 The position will be located at one of our Resilience network offices.
 Responsibilities
 Ensure the quality and compliance of GMP activities with respect to internal and/or customer procedures as well as FDA, ICH, EU and country specific regulations
 Provide Quality oversight to COTS Digital Systems implementation projects across all phases of the System Development Lifecycle and associated artifacts across Resilience network.
 Support initiatives and projects to establish a corporate-wide Digital Systems Governance Program (development and lifecycle management of policies and standards in support of deployment and maintenance of computerized systems).
 Support development of a risk management strategy for DI controls (including testing) of digital systems procured by and/or designed/developed in house at Resilience; collaborate with stakeholders (including sites, franchises) to institutionalize the strategy across the Resilience network.
 Prepare and conduct or assist/oversee Digital System / Vendor audits per established risk based strategy.
 Conduct/oversee of training of Resilience personnel on CSV, Change Control, Data Integrity and on relevant Quality SOPs
 Assist in establishing, and facilitate the Governance boards such as Computer Systems Validation and/or Change Review Board.
 Establish and manage the GXP applicability and risk profile determination of GXP systems procured and designed/developed within Resilience.
 Assist in developing systems strategy that pilots and implements efficient cutting-edge technology on new platforms, including intelligent robotic, automation solutions utilizing artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) technologies
 Maintain systems in a state of inspection readiness at all time.
 Contribute to the development and implementation of the global digital compliance strategy
 Qualifications
 Comprehensive knowledge of global GMP regulatory requirements
 Hands on experience in developing and managing an effective Computer Systems Assurance program in support of COTs and GMP computerized systems to meet Digital needs.
 Hands-on experience in building and managing team focused on providing quality oversight of computerized systems validation program
 Demonstrated experience in assuring data integrity controls are designed and adhered to in Computerized Systems.
 Excellent oral and written communication skills with strong technical writing experience required
 Ability to synthesize data and summarize outcomes to provide recommendations on a compliant path forward
 Demonstrated ability to set goals, perform long-term project planning, team building, budgeting and operational excellence
 Demonstrated ability to successfully execute responsibilities in a fast-pace environment, collaborating across multiple sites and stakeholders
 Ability to travel
 Requirements
 Bachelorâ€™s degree or higher in IT, Life Sciences, Chemistry, Engineering, or related field
